# Accessibility Guidelines

## Semantic HTML
- Use proper HTML5 semantic elements
- Implement proper heading hierarchy
- Use proper form elements
- Implement proper table structure
- Use proper list elements

## ARIA Attributes
- Use proper ARIA labels
- Implement proper ARIA descriptions
- Use proper ARIA states
- Implement proper ARIA live regions
- Use proper ARIA landmarks

## Keyboard Navigation
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Implement proper tab order
- Use proper keyboard shortcuts
- Handle keyboard events properly
- Implement proper focus management

## Screen Reader Support
- Test with screen readers
- Use proper alt text for images
- Implement proper form labels
- Use proper heading structure
- Implement proper skip links

## Color and Contrast
- Ensure proper color contrast ratios
- Don't rely solely on color for information
- Test with color blindness simulators
- Use proper color combinations
- Implement proper dark mode support

## Focus Management
- Implement proper focus indicators
- Handle focus properly in modals
- Use proper focus trapping
- Implement proper focus restoration
- Use proper focus order

## Form Accessibility
- Use proper form labels
- Implement proper error messages
- Use proper field validation
- Implement proper form feedback
- Use proper form structure

## Dynamic Content
- Handle dynamic content updates properly
- Use proper ARIA live regions
- Implement proper loading states
- Handle error states properly
- Use proper progress indicators

## Testing
- Test with accessibility tools
- Test with screen readers
- Test keyboard navigation
- Test color contrast
- Test with different devices

## Performance
- Ensure accessibility doesn't impact performance
- Use proper lazy loading
- Implement proper caching
- Monitor accessibility metrics
- Optimize for accessibility

## Best Practices
- Follow WCAG 2.1 guidelines
- Use proper accessibility patterns
- Implement proper error handling
- Use proper testing tools
- Document accessibility features
